Itâ€™s been a good 24 hours for Michael Bloomberg. Early this morning, on the brink of the deadline to do so, the former New York City mayor qualified for Wednesdayâ€™s Democratic presidential debate thanks to a NPR/PBS NewsHour/Marist College poll that gave him 19 percent of the national primary vote. Heâ€™s up to 16.3 percent in our national polling average â€” essentially tying him with former Vice President Joe Biden for the first time. However, heâ€™s still 9 points behind front-runner Sen. Bernie Sanders, and â€” by Bloombergâ€™s own design â€” it will be a couple weeks before we know how much actual voter support Bloomberg has.
[Our Latest Forecast: Who Will Win The 2020 Democratic Primary?]
