From a poll with 1,587 respondents, conducted Jan. 17-20, 2020.
We also asked respondents an open-ended question that allowed them to share a few words for how theyâ€™d describe the impeachment process. In the most recent wave of our survey, 24 percent of Republicans mentioned â€œwasteâ€ in their description of the impeachment process, a notable increase over the last two waves, when around 17 percent of GOP respondents used the word. The words mentioned by Democrats, meanwhile, have been all over the map, with â€œnecessaryâ€ and â€œTrumpâ€ showing up the most â€” but not nearly as frequently as â€œwasteâ€ did among Republicans.
