FiveThirtyEightâ€™s partisan lean metric is the average difference between how a state votes and how the country votes overall, with 2016 presidential election results weighted at 50 percent, 2012 presidential election results weighted at 25 percent and results from elections for the state legislature weighted at 25 percent. Note that the partisan leans in this article were calculated before the 2018 elections; we havenâ€™t calculated FiveThirtyEight partisan leans that incorporate the midterm results yet.
