Thereâ€™s also little evidence that the remaining â€œmajorâ€ candidates based on FiveThirtyEightâ€™s criteria will qualify for the sixth debate. Only author and motivational speaker Marianne Williamson has a real shot at reaching the 200,000-donor threshold â€” she previously met the 130,000 requirement for the September debate. But her campaign hasnâ€™t reported an updated contributor count for the fifth or sixth debates, and even if she did hit the donor mark, Williamson is unlikely to get enough support in the polls to make the November debate, much less the December one.
Although many candidates will reach the donor threshold for the sixth debate â€” eight already have and more likely will â€” it looks like the stricter polling requirement will make it tougher sledding for many of them. So donâ€™t be shocked if fewer than 10 candidates make the December stage.\n|end|\n
