Now, because more voters list Biden as their first choice than list Sanders or Warren, he probably does have his fair share of begrudging supporters. But itâ€™s a fallacy to say that Biden doesnâ€™t have enthusiastic supporters also. According to national polls, he has plenty â€” about as many as Sanders or Warren. On top of that, he also gets support from other Democrats who are less enthusiastic but support him for other reasons, e.g. electability. Those two paths to support are why Bidenâ€™s polling at almost 30 percent while Sanders and Warren are closer to 15 percent.
