And before, you asked me if I trust the government, and I certainly donâ€™t trust this administration, and I donâ€™t trust the American electorate to constantly produce politicians that I do trust. What I do trust is a good system of checks and balances and incentives; that part is very important, too. If you donâ€™t have the ability to audit the surveilers, youâ€™re asking people to trust the government en masse, but also then youâ€™re saying everyone who enters the government has to achieve that level of trust, which is crazy.
