After the debates, I issued a set of my periodically updating, not-to-be-taken-too-seriously nomination tiers, which reflect my subjective impression of the candidatesâ€™ relative likelihood of winning the nomination (i.e. thereâ€™s no statistical model behind these). But that was based on a lot of educated guessing of how voters would react to the debates. Now that we have actual data in hand, a few further tweaks are in order.
For the Democratic nomination, as revised on Aug. 8, 2019
