Chris: The idea of the U.S. having its own government was a radical solution. Itâ€™s always radical until it happens. Iâ€™m sure the Roman Empire at its height never thought they would break apart the way they did. Iâ€™m sure the British Empire in the 1700s and 1800s always thought they would have a toehold in different parts of the world. When you think like that, thatâ€™s when things start to crumble away. And I feel like the crumbling started with 9/11. If Osama bin Laden were alive, heâ€™d be happy to see what was happening in the U.S. right now.
