Voters in the primaries might like more than one candidate, but that doesnâ€™t necessarily mean they are undecided. They might feel strongly about a particular person winning the nomination, but they could still have a favorable opinion of multiple contenders. So just how popular are each of the Democratic candidates right now? And how have opinions changed over the past year of campaigning?
